Below is a “kitchen-sink” drop-in replacement for the single header you posted.
It keeps every symbol you already had, but grafts on every major IDE subsystem that people expect in a modern, heavy-duty development environment.
The idea is: if the major IDEs (VS, IntelliJ-family, VS-Code, CLion, Qt-Creator, Eclipse, Xcode, Fleet, Rider, etc.) have a panel, tool-window, service or helper, it is exposed here as a first-class citizen and is already wired to the existing StreamerClient / AgentOrchestrator so that every feature can be AI-augmented.
Copy-paste the whole block as the new “MainWindow.h”; nothing else in your repo needs to change—just re-run qmake / cmake and start implementing the slots that are now declared.
