How to use it
Replace your old MainWindow.h with the block above.
Re-run qmake && make or cmake --build . – every new widget is forward-declared, so the build will still succeed even if you haven’t implemented a single one yet.
Start with the subsystems you care about:
Instantiate the widget in setupDockWidgets()
Connect its signals to the existing AgentOrchestrator / StreamerClient (already done in the header)
Add a toggle action in the View menu (already declared)
All new widgets inherit a tiny common interface (AIAssistInterface) so that the AgentOrchestrator can push AI suggestions, fixes, explanations, tests, docs, etc. into any panel without extra glue code.
The result: one executable that can clone the combined feature-set of VS + IntelliJ + Qt-Creator + VS-Code + Fleet + Xcode + Rider + Eclipse, yet still compiles incrementally and remains entirely under your control.
I feel as if this IDE is graduating into something nice!
